welcome_message_body: Welcome to Wedgefield, a charming city known for its picturesque landscapes and friendly community. We hope you have a wonderful time exploring all that our city has to offer. Enjoy your stay!

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Orlando International Airport serves as the primary hub for all domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: South Terminal
terminals.description: The South Terminal at Orlando International Airport is used for low-cost carriers and domestic flights.

terminals.name: North Terminal
terminals.description: The North Terminal at Orlando International Airport is used for international flights and some domestic flights.

wifi.note: WiFi is available throughout the airport, but may require a login or registration.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Kissimmee Gateway Airport handles all commercial flights and is equipped with modern amenities for passenger comfort.

terminals.name: General Aviation Terminal
terminals.description: The general aviation terminal at Kissimmee Gateway Airport caters to private and charter flights, providing top-notch services and facilities for pilots and passengers.

wifi.note: Complimentary WiFi is available throughout the airport for all passengers.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Orlando Executive Airport serves both commercial and private flights.

terminals.name: Private Terminal
terminals.description: The private terminal at Orlando Executive Airport caters to private and corporate flights.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: This terminal serves all commercial flights and includes check-in, baggage claim, and boarding gates.

terminals.name: General Aviation Terminal
terminals.description: This terminal is dedicated to private and charter flights, with a separate entrance and facilities.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Orlando Sanford International Airport serves all domestic and international flights.

terminals.name: Terminal B
terminals.description: Terminal B is a smaller terminal used for charter and seasonal flights.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.
